OL,3,CCould this be the world's longest
OL,4,Cserving referee?
OL,6,F"Allegedly, I missed penalties and
OL,7,Fgave offside goals, everything a
OL,8,Freferee shouldn't do, I did. I walked
OL,9,Fhome from the game soaked and said to
OL,10,Fmyself 'What am I doing here?'. But,
OL,11,Fthe following Saturday I was back out
OL,12,Fagain."
OL,14,FKen, who began refereeing in 1964,
OL,15,Fsays he's taken charge of over 5,000
OL,16,Fgames throughout his career.
OL,18,FA member of the West Wales Football
OL,19,FAssociation, Ken is currently a
OL,20,Freferee in the Swansea Senior League
OL,21,Fofficiating each Saturday.
